<br /><br />
<b><font class="print-title">More on Focus Items</font></b><br /><br />
<font class="print-sub">Articles / EverQuest News<br />
<b>Date:</b> Jun 04, 2002 - 01:24 PM</font>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>
<font class="print-normal">As reported on <a href="http://www.graffe.com/">Graffe's Wizard Compilation</a> and <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/">CastersRealm</a> there are changes coming to existing items with the next patch. Hopefully this is slated for the patch on June 5th (tomorrow).<br /><br />
&lt;hr noshade&gt;Snip<center></center>
This patch has a large selection of focus effects added to existing items. This is the first round of non-summoned focus items, and the goal is to get a decent amount of them into the hands of players without creating a bottleneck camp for new items. This round of focus items includes over 150 items with focus effects being added retroactively, and should provide a good foundation for moving forward with new focus items in the future. 
<p>
</p>
Additional focus effects and items will be added in the next round, specifically to higher end content as we create more specialized effects to use on these items. 
<p>
</p>
- Rich
<p>
</p>
Here is a list of items currently known from the Test Server as reported on Graffes:
<ul>
<li>Polished Bone Bracelet - Affliction Efficiency I 
<li>Bracelet of Woven Grass - Spell Haste I 
<li>Golden Efreeti Boots - Enchancement Haste II 
<li>Damask Robe - Extended Enhancement I 
<li>Ring of Goblin Lords - Affliction Haste I 
<li>Green Silken Drape - Affliction Haste II 
<li>Moonstone Ring - Extended Range II 
<li>Batskull Earring - Reagent Conservation I 
<li>Runed Mithril Bracers - Reagent Conservation III 
<li>Azure Sleeves - Improved Damage I 
<li>Turtle Shell Helm - Improved Healing I 
<li>Sarnak Arcane Fetish - Improved Healing II 
<li>Chipped Bone Bracelet - Affliction Efficiency II 
<li>Savant's Cap - Reagent Conservation II 
</ul>
<br />
<br />
</font>
